snippet: A townhouse on one of the most picturesque blocks in the West Village, built in 1833 on farmland once owned by John Jacob Astor.
abstract: Historic five-story Federal-style brick Townhouse on one of West Village's most picturesque blocks is for sale for $23.9 million; home was built in 1833 on farmland once owned by John Jacob Astor.
lead_paragraph: A townhouse on one of the most picturesque blocks in the West Village, built in 1833 on farmland once owned by John Jacob Astor.
